original: Johansson, Gustaf Arvid, komminister, Hedekas, f. 21/1/07 i Tanum, Gbgs o. Boh. 1. — Stud:ex. i Lund 27, teol. fil. ex. 29, teol. kand. o. prakt, teol. prov 33, prästv. f. Gb’gs istift 34. Tjg. s. pastorsadj. i Skaftö o. Vinberg ’samt s. past:adj. i Gunnarp, ikommin. i Sanne ised. 41.
translated: Johansson, Gustaf Arvid, vicar, Hedekas, born on January 21, 1907 in Tanum, Gothenburg and Bohuslän County. He graduated from Lund University with a degree in theology in 1927 and passed his theology exams in 1929. He completed practical theology training and passed his priestly exam in Gothenburg in 1933, then was ordained as a priest in the Gothenburg diocese in 1934. He served as an assistant pastor in Skaftö, Vinberg and Gunnarp, and was appointed as a vicar in Sanne in 1941. He got married in 19xx.
